***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 1998 09:22:51 +0800
Source: Hospital Authority Internet Homepage, Hong Kong
<http://www.ha.org.hk/main.htm>
Via: Dr. M. Vadivale <vale@pop.jaring.my>

[The following is a topics outline of guidelines for handling enterovirus
71 infections as prepared by the Hong Kong Hospital Authority. The
document is too long to post in its entirety, but it considers issues of
importance for any region afflicted with such outbreaks. ProMED-mail is
posting this information to facilitate access.
Subscribers who lack web access, and have e-mail service only may access
this document by sending a message to getweb@usa.healthnet.org that says
'get http://www.ha.org.hk/clnguide/ev71v2.htm' without the ' marks. The
document should be delivered in readable form via e-mail within seconds. -
Mod.ES]

